This issue is because the selector prefix for xpath is just `//`. It doesn't default to xpath. 

We could add `(//` as a prefix for an xpath selector, but my preference is that we leave it as is because it's simple. 

@aaltat if you agree we can close this ticket. If not, we should open another ticket on the xpath prefix.

